-- Telekom Slovenije Names Skobe as CEO for Four-Year Term
-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 2012-07-12T08:13:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-12/telekom-slovenije-names-skobe-as-ceo-for-four-year-term.html
Telekom Slovenije (TLSG)  Group d.d. named
Rudolf Skobe as the new chief executive officer of the Slovenian
state-owned phone company for a four-year term.  Skobe, 39, will replace Ivica Kranjcevic from Sept. 1, the
Ljubljana-based company said in a regulatory statement today.
Skobe has been with the company since 1998, starting at the
internet unit, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  